&lt;p&gt;Hello, dear all!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Legendary Tulip is back and has put on a veil of mystery!&lt;br /&gt;And I have a lot of new caches and prizes waiting for you! [:)]&lt;br /&gt;Are you ready for this new quest?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Well then, let the fun begin!&lt;/p&gt;<br />
&lt;p&gt;Please register your participation &lt;a href=&quot;http://laleaua.opencaching.ro/page/2014/register&quot;&gt;HERE&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
<p><em>This <a href='http://www.opencaching.ro/viewcache.php?cacheid=1'>geocache</a> description comes from the <a href='http://www.opencaching.ro/'>Opencaching.RO</a> site.</em></p>

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;ctl00_ContentBody_LongDescription&quot;&gt;Friday, April 11th, 8:30PM&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;<br />
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;ctl00_ContentBody_LongDescription&quot;&gt;The Tulip will welcome first comers with fun and games.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
<p><em>This <a href='http://www.opencaching.ro/viewcache.php?cacheid=3'>geocache</a> description comes from the <a href='http://www.opencaching.ro/'>Opencaching.RO</a> site.</em></p>

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;ctl00_ContentBody_LongDescription&quot;&gt;Saturday, April 12th, 23:00 EET, Trivale park.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;<br />
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;ctl00_ContentBody_LongDescription&quot;&gt;The forest is full of spirits. The nearby monastery is well known for performing exorcism on &quot;possessed&quot; people. The spirit is released into the forest and may be looking for another host. Do you fear the dark? Are you afraid of spirits?&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Let's exorcise !&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
<p><em>This <a href='http://www.opencaching.ro/viewcache.php?cacheid=4'>geocache</a> description comes from the <a href='http://www.opencaching.ro/'>Opencaching.RO</a> site.</em></p>

&lt;p&gt;This is a nice little park built recently in the neighbourhood. It is one of the few parks which are full of grass and surrounded by trees.&lt;/p&gt;<br />
&lt;p&gt;Be very careful with the guard!&lt;/p&gt;
<p><em>This <a href='http://www.opencaching.ro/viewcache.php?cacheid=36'>geocache</a> description comes from the <a href='http://www.opencaching.ro/'>Opencaching.RO</a> site.</em></p>

&lt;p&gt;This is the actual house of culture in Mangalia city. This building is one of the most important ones here, yet almost forgotten.&lt;/p&gt;<br />
&lt;p&gt;Note: GPS signal is very weak.&lt;/p&gt;
<p><em>This <a href='http://www.opencaching.ro/viewcache.php?cacheid=44'>geocache</a> description comes from the <a href='http://www.opencaching.ro/'>Opencaching.RO</a> site.</em></p>

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold; color: orange;&quot;&gt;Moving clockwise&lt;/span&gt; around the star, can you reveal the hidden five-letter word?&lt;/p&gt;<br />
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: center; margin-top: 1em;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://laleaua.opencaching.ro/page/2014/files/steaua_misterioasa.png&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
<p><em>This <a href='http://www.opencaching.ro/viewcache.php?cacheid=46'>geocache</a> description comes from the <a href='http://www.opencaching.ro/'>Opencaching.RO</a> site.</em></p>

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 1.6em;&quot;&gt;These &lt;strong&gt;stairs&lt;/strong&gt; connects the neighborhood Gavana to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Gîrlei&lt;/strong&gt; zone&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 1.6em;&quot;&gt;. Stairs are often used by pedestrians crossing the area and in winter, the hill is used as tobogganing. Nearby is a small landscaped park. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;<br />
&lt;p&gt;Neither in town we escaped from grills; the locals make barbecues under the pylon.&lt;/p&gt;
<p><em>This <a href='http://www.opencaching.ro/viewcache.php?cacheid=48'>geocache</a> description comes from the <a href='http://www.opencaching.ro/'>Opencaching.RO</a> site.</em></p>

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold; color: orange;&quot;&gt;Războieni neighborhood&lt;/span&gt; According to official data, in 2008, Războieni neighborhood numbered almost 15,000 residents, representing 8.3% of the city's population.&lt;br /&gt; The poorest communist-era blocks neighborhood. Is also considered a hood which is populated by gypsyes.&lt;/p&gt;<br />
&lt;p&gt;This is the end of the line for several busses that cross the city.&lt;br /&gt; So old is this station that permanent residents got a hold of it.&lt;br /&gt; Find the bus lines still entirely visible, put them together, double, and find the bEAST.&lt;/p&gt;
<p><em>This <a href='http://www.opencaching.ro/viewcache.php?cacheid=49'>geocache</a> description comes from the <a href='http://www.opencaching.ro/'>Opencaching.RO</a> site.</em></p>
